The paper deals with the spanning properties of a graph defined by cones, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of spanners suggests that the paper may also be relevant to distributed computing (cs.DS) and network algorithms (cs.NA). The analysis of the graph's behavior for sets of points in convex and non-convex positions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational topology (cs.SI).
